# 3. Scale up

Whiteboard design that scales the infrastructure by splitting each component
onto its own dedicated server and clustering the load balancers.

## Diagram

```
                                  ( User )
                                      |
                          https://www.foobar.com
                                      |
                                      v
                 +-------------------------------------+
                 |   Load balancer cluster (HAProxy)   |
                 |                                     |
                 |   LB1  <----- VRRP/keepalived ----->  LB2
                 |  (active)        (cluster)        (passive)
                 +------------------+------------------+
                                    |
                  distributes traffic to web tier
                                    |
                                    v
                       +-------------------------+
                       |   Web server            |
                       |   Nginx                 |
                       +------------+------------+
                                    |
                            forwards dynamic requests
                                    |
                                    v
                       +-------------------------+
                       |   Application server    |
                       |   (app files / code)    |
                       +------------+------------+
                                    |
                              queries data
                                    |
                                    v
                       +-------------------------+
                       |   Database server       |
                       |   MySQL                 |
                       +-------------------------+
```

## Why each additional element is added

- **An extra server + splitting the components:** the web server, application
  server, and database are each moved onto their **own dedicated server**. This
  lets each tier be scaled, tuned, secured, and maintained independently. A
  spike in application CPU no longer starves the database; each component can
  use the full resources of its machine and be replicated on its own.

- **A second load balancer, clustered with the first (HAProxy cluster):** the
  two load balancers are set up as a cluster (e.g. using keepalived with a
  shared/virtual IP via VRRP). This removes the load balancer as a single point
  of failure: typically one is **active** and the other **passive**, and if the
  active LB fails, the passive one takes over the virtual IP and keeps traffic
  flowing.

## Application server vs web server

- **Web server (e.g. Nginx):** handles HTTP/HTTPS requests, serves **static**
  content (HTML, CSS, JS, images) directly, and acts as a reverse proxy. It is
  optimized for fast, concurrent handling of many connections and for delivering
  files. It does not contain the business logic.

- **Application server:** runs the **application code / business logic**. It
  generates **dynamic** content, processes the requests the web server proxies
  to it, talks to the database, and builds the responses. It is the runtime
  environment for your code base.

In short: the web server speaks HTTP and delivers content/static assets, while
the application server executes your code to produce the dynamic content. The
web server typically sits in front and forwards dynamic requests to the
application server.
